<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Vision" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Vision,</orth> sight; 1) the faculty of seeing: <emph>nor his</emph> (my eye's) <cit><quote>own v. holds what it doth catch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 113.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 113, 8</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) something seen; a) something seen in reality: <cit><quote>to a v. so apparent rumour cannot be mute,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 270</bibl></cit> (perhaps used here with intended ambiguity).
<lb />b) a supernatural or imaginary appearance seen in waking or dreaming: <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 118</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.176.270" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.371" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 371</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 81</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.433.81" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 433</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 52</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 2, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 1, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.346" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 346</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.467" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 467</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 3, 69</bibl>.
